# Sepolia Testnet Configuration
SEPOLIA_RPC_URL=https://sepolia.infura.io/v3/YOUR_INFURA_PROJECT_ID
PRIVATE_KEY=your_wallet_private_key_here
ETHERSCAN_API_KEY=your_etherscan_api_key_here

# Server Configuration
PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=development

# Contract Addresses (will be populated after deployment)
COLLECTION_CONTRACT_ADDRESS=

# API Keys
INFURA_PROJECT_ID=your_infura_project_id
ALCHEMY_API_KEY=your_alchemy_api_key

# Pinata IPFS Configuration (get keys from https://app.pinata.cloud/)
PINATA_API_KEY=your_pinata_api_key
PINATA_SECRET_KEY=your_pinata_secret_key
IPFS_GATEWAY=https://gateway.pinata.cloud/ipfs/
## IPFS/Pinata Integration for Phase 3 ✅

Added off-chain IPFS storage for detailed herb data:

### Files Created:

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| [`backend/services/pinataService.js`](backend/services/pinataService.js) | Main Pinata/IPFS service |
| [`backend/routes/pinata.js`](backend/routes/pinata.js) | API routes for IPFS operations |
| [`backend/services/uploadService.js`](backend/services/uploadService.js) | File upload middleware (multer) |

### API Endpoints:

| Endpoint | Method | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| `/api/pinata/test` | GET | Test Pinata connection |
| `/api/pinata/upload-metadata` | POST | Upload herb metadata JSON |
| `/api/pinata/upload-image` | POST | Upload herb image |
| `/api/pinata/upload-batch` | POST | Full batch upload (metadata + image) |
| `/api/pinata/unpin/:hash` | DELETE | Remove from IPFS |
| `/api/pinata/gateway/:hash` | GET | Get gateway URL |

### Configuration:
Updated [`backend/.env.example`](backend/.env.example) with:
```
PINATA_API_KEY=your_pinata_api_key
PINATA_SECRET_KEY=your_pinata_secret_key
IPFS_GATEWAY=https://gateway.pinata.cloud/ipfs/
```

### How it works:
1. Collector uploads herb image → Pinata → IPFS hash
2. Metadata created with IPFS image hash → Pinata → IPFS hash
3. IPFS hash stored on-chain in HerbNFT `tokenURI`
4. Full metadata available off-chain via IPFS gateway

